Key Match Events: Kevon Looney provided invaluable minutes off the bench, scoring eight points on 4-6 shooting from the field and grabbing eight rebounds in just over 20 minutes of action.
Looney dished out three assists, showcasing his playmaking abilities.
Looney helped Golden State contain Pistons center Jalen Duren, who finished with eight points, 12 boards, and three blocks.
Post-Match Reflections: Warriors head coach Steve Kerr lauded Kevon Looney's performance, calling him a winner and highlighting his high-IQ basketball, patient decision-making, and tenacious activity on the glass.
